xxl.core.collections.bags

Interface FIFOBag<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements this bag is able to store.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Bag<E>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayBag, DynamicArrayBag, ListBag

    public interface FIFOBag<E>
extends Bag<E>
    The interface FIFO bag represents a FIFO (first in, first out) iteration over the elements of a bag. This interface predefines a FIFO strategy for addition of elements.

    • Method Detail

      • fifoCursor

        Cursor<E> fifoCursor()
        Returns a cursor representing a FIFO (first in, first out) iteration over the elements in this bag. The cursor is specifying a view on the elements of this bag so that closing the cursor takes no effect on the bag (e.g., not closing the bag). The behavior of the cursor is unspecified if this bag is modified while the cursor is in progress in any way other than by calling the methods of the cursor. So, when the implementation of this cursor cannot guarantee that the cursor is in a valid state after modifing the underlying bag every method of the cursor except close() should throw a ConcurrentModificationException.
        Returns:
        a cursor representing a FIFO (first in, first out) iteration over the elements in this bag.
